  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Triangles <math alttext=\"upper A upper B upper C\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>A</mi>\n\t<mi>B</mi>\n\t<mi>C</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"upper D upper E upper F\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>D</mi>\n\t<mi>E</mi>\n\t<mi>F</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math> are congruent, where <math alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi>\n</math> corresponds to <math alttext=\"upper D\"><mi>D</mi>\n</math>, and <math alttext=\"upper B\"><mi>B</mi>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"upper E\"><mi>E</mi>\n</math> are right angles. The measure of angle <math alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi>\n</math> is <math alttext=\"27 degree\"><mrow><mn>27</mn></mrow><mo>&#176;</mo></math>. What is the measure, in degrees, of angle <math alttext=\"upper F\"><mi>F</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
